gress Party Government has decided to include tenant farmers in Rythu Bharosa scheme as they are excluded from the Pradhan Mantri Kisan Samman Nidhi (PM-Kisan) scheme.AP YSR Rythu Bharosa Scheme List of BeneficiariesThe Real Time Governance Society (RTGS) is expected to prepare the AP YSR Rythu Bharosa Scheme list of beneficiaries. There are around 66,54,891 farmers which are expected to be the beneficiaries of this investment support scheme in Andhra Pradesh. Around 15.36 lakh tenant farmers will also get benefited from farm investment support scheme. A total of 64.06 farmers in Andhra Pradesh, both landowners and tenants, are eligible for the YSR Rythu Bharosa scheme.Each landowner farmer has already received 2 installments of Rs. 4,000 (from a total of Rs 6,000 per annum) under the PM-Kisan scheme, Now AP govt. will release its assured amount of Rs. 6,500 to each landowner / farmers. The tenant farmers are getting Rs. 12,500 each in a single tranche from 15 October 2019.The YSRCP government had initially planned to give the farm investment support under YSR Rythu Bharosa separately, but later merged it with the PM-kisan scheme for the landowners. The installments of YSR Rythu Bharosa would be credited directly into the bank accounts of the farmer through direct benefit transfer (DBT) mode. AP govt. has set aside a budget of Rs. 8,750 crore for the scheme.Till date, there are around 6,04,676 farmers unsurveyed. There are total 47,71,005 farmer\u2019s families while there are 61,999 ROFR cultivators.Also Read \u2013 AP YSR Pension Kanuka Scheme 2020 Also Read \u2013 AP YSR Aarogyasri Scheme 2020  Sarkari Yojana App - Download Now Source / Reference Link: https://www.thehansindia.com/andhra-pradesh/cm-ys-jagan-takes-key-decision-during-agriculture-department-review-535549  at  "}